# Example environment file. Copy to the real per-env filename and fill in values:
#   cp .env.example .env.development
#   cp .env.example .env.staging
#   cp .env.example .env.production
# Real .env files are gitignored and MUST NOT be committed.
#
# Issue #20: ALL API base URLs MUST use https:// (TLS). The only permitted
# cleartext (http://) exception is a LOCAL dev host (the Android emulator's
# host alias 10.0.2.2, or localhost) in .env.development only — never in
# staging or production.
#
# Two backends are configured per environment:
#   BASE_API_URL -> Main API
#   VIAL_API_URL -> Vial API
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# DEVELOPMENT (.env.development)
#   Local dev may use cleartext ONLY against localhost / the emulator host.
#   On the Android emulator, 10.0.2.2 maps to the host machine's localhost.
#   Switch to https:// for any non-local dev host.
#   Example:
#     BASE_API_URL=http://10.0.2.2:8100/api
#     VIAL_API_URL=http://10.0.2.2:5000
#
# STAGING (.env.staging)
#   MUST be https:// — no cleartext allowed.
#     BASE_API_URL=https://TODO(host): set real staging Main API host/api
#     VIAL_API_URL=https://TODO(host): set real staging Vial API host
#
# PRODUCTION (.env.production)
#   MUST be https:// — no cleartext allowed.
#     BASE_API_URL=https://TODO(host): set real production Main API host/api
#     VIAL_API_URL=https://TODO(host): set real production Vial API host
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# The active values below are the safe https:// defaults used when this file is
# copied verbatim (e.g. in CI, where .env.* are generated from this example).
# Replace TODO(host) with the real host for each environment before shipping.

BASE_API_URL=https://TODO-set-real-host.example.invalid
VIAL_API_URL=https://TODO-set-real-host.example.invalid
